    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="410"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.428/597</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geddes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 354</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to invite reference to Mr.
                    Lindsay’s note No. 224 of April 12th last<note n="8" xml:id="d410fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> and to inform you that the Canadian Government are pressing
                    to know when the signature of the Fisheries Treaty can be arranged.</p>
                <p>At the same time and with reference to Mr. Lindsay’s note No. 181 of March
                        23rd,<note n="8" xml:id="d410fn9">Not printed.</note> I am asked to
                    ascertain whether the United States Government are now prepared to consent to
                    the publication of the report of the International Fisheries Commission.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. C. Geddes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
